In a cricket match, George scores double~the runs in each round compared to the one before. If George scored $$1$$ run in the first round, in which round did he score $$32$$ runs?
(A) 4^{th}
(B) 7^{th}
(C) 6^{th}
(D) 8^{th}
(E) 5^{th}

A number is opposite to $$-\frac{1}{3}$$ and the aboslute value of that number is~\uline{~~~~~~~~~~}~.
(A) 3
(B) -3
(C) \frac{1}{3}
(D) -\frac{1}{3}

A ball is thrown from the top of a building and each time the ball bounces to half of its previous height. If the height of the building is $$512$$ meters, which time does it bounce when it bounces to a height of $$16$$ meters?
(A) 4^{th}
(B) 7^{th}
(C) 6^{th}
(D) 8^{th}
(E) 5^{th}

